Package Enginegames

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Tickable
    an interface, which makes Classes able to be called every tick by an engine.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    AdvancedImage
    An extension of BufferedImages, able to be cloned, having a default positioning when drawn with supporting functions
    Button
    A basic Button one is able to put into ones world.
    Dialog
    A class to ask the User for input.
    Engine  
    Engine.TickEngine
    Gets generated every tick.
    GameUI
    The JFrame the worlds get shown on.
    Label
    an empty button, made just to show some ~~pride~~ text
    Main  
    MouseEventInfo
    Wrapper class, to contain both, the event type of a mouseevent, as well as the event itself.
    ScrollButton
    A Button with a list of options to choose from.
    Textfield
    A textfield, used to enter Text or numbers by the user.
    Utils
    A utility class capable of loading images, extracting assets from a compressed jar etc.
    World
    The world everything takes place in.
    WorldObj
    superclass of all objects being able to be added to the world
    WorldUI  
  • Enum Summary
    Enum Description
    AdvancedImage.ImagePosition
    Enum for how the Image is positioned, when drawn by a supporting class
    AdvancedImage.ImageSizing
    an enum for what to do, if the image doesn't fit the bounds of what it is drawn onto
